Enclosing class:
SortingMetadata
public static enum SortingMetadata.State
extends Enum<SortingMetadata.State>

A SortingMetadata.State determines the lifecycle phases of a SortableResult in Accumulo.

LOADING means that new records are actively being loaded and queries can start; however, only the columns specified as being indexed when the SortableResult was defined can be guaranteed to exist. Meaning, calls to Cosmos#index(SortableResult, Iterable) will not block queries from running while the index is being updated. Obviously, queries in this state are not guaranteed to be the column result set for a SortableResult

LOADED means that the Cosmos client writing results has completed.

ERROR means that there an error in the loading of the data for the given SortableResult and processing has ceased.

DELETING means that a client has called Cosmos.delete(SortableResult) and the results are in the process of being deleted.

UNKNOWN means that the software is unaware of the given SortableResult
